Forces loyal to President Joseph Momohfoiled an attempted coup apparently led by senior policeofficers in Sierra Leone, government sources said.    The revolt included an unsuccessful raid on a Freetownmilitary arsenal during which a police officer's driver wasshot dead, they said. Police sources said a senior policemanwas arrested on suspicion of leading the coup attempt.    There were no immediate reports in the official news media.    Police and troops patrolled the centre of the capital andthere was no sign of further trouble. REUTER&#3;